profile_positions.description:
Shell Downstream Businesses, required to comply with the new Shell security standard. Terry was hired as the cluster Project manager to enhance the project structure and improve reporting, escalation and remediation in each of the clusters including tasks:
•	obtaining buy in form each refinery senior management
•	extensive communication and working  other Shell infrastructure delivery parties 
•	delivery of  scoping documents for the downstream Europe  operating units and refineries certification; 
•	management of  the operating units project plans and certification; 
•	leading the internal Pre-audits and managing the external (KPMG) audits; 
He successfully completed the Shell Trust Domain (now called ISS-Information Security Standard) certification, subject to external KPMG TD security audits, within target deadline of the first quarter of 2006 for 6 countries and operating units in the Mediterranean and the 9 Refineries for Downstream Europe. He received a Shell special recognition award and bonus from Shell for this role.
